{
  "texts": [
    "Luciferin was added underneath the transwell insert and allowed to incubate for 10 min before bioluminescence measurement on an AMI optical imaging system.",
    "All work was approved by the Institutional Animal Care and Use Committee at the University of North Carolina-Chapel Hill.",
    "To prepare extracts containing soluble and chromatin-associated proteins, monolayers of cultured cells typically in 10-cm plates were washed twice in ice-cold PBS and lysed in 200-300 µl of ice-cold cytoskeleton buffer (CSK buffer; 10 mM Pipes, pH 6.8, 100 mM NaCl, 300 mM sucrose, 3 mM MgCl 2, 1 mM EGTA, 1 mM dithiothreitol, 0.1 mM ATP, 10 mM NaF, and 0.1% Triton X-100) freshly supplemented with protease inhibitor cocktail and PhosSTOP.",
    "Lysates were centrifuged at 1500 g for 4 min to remove the CSK-insoluble nuclei.",
    "The detergent-insoluble nuclear fractions were washed once with 300 µl of CSK buffer and then resuspended in a minimal volume of CSK."
  ]
}